<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <%- include('head') %>
  <title><%= locals.title %></title>
  <meta name="description" content="<%= locals.description %>" />
  <meta name="robots" content="noindex, follow" />
  <meta property="og:title" content="<%= locals.title %>" />
  <meta property="og:description" content="<%= locals.description %>" />
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://oldschoolgames.eu/dmca" />
  <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
  <meta property="og:site_name" content="OldSchoolGames" />
</head>

<body class="layout">
  <%- include('navbar') %> <%- include('left-sidebar') %>
  <main>
    <div class="container">
      <%- include('flash') %>
      <section>
        <h1 class="text-lg" style="margin-bottom: 5px">
          DMCA / Copyright Policy
        </h1>
        <p style="
              color: rgb(var(--muted-rgb));
              font-size: 0.9em;
              margin-bottom: 25px;
            ">
          Last updated: March 2026
        </p>

        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px">
          OldSchoolGames.eu respects the intellectual property rights of
          others and expects users to do the same. This page describes our
          policy regarding copyright infringement claims under the Digital
          Millennium Copyright Act (DMCA) and equivalent European copyright
          law.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin: 25px 0 10px">
          Our Approach to Games
        </h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 15px">
          This site is a non-commercial hobby project. The games hosted here
          are believed to fall into one of the following categories:
        </p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 15px">
          <li>
            Games officially released as <strong>freeware</strong> by their
            publishers or copyright holders
          </li>
          <li>
            Games whose publishers are no longer active and for which no
            commercial version is available
          </li>
          <li>
            Games hosted for historical preservation and educational purposes
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px">
          We do not generate revenue from the games distributed on this site.
          However, we understand that the legal status of some titles may be
          unclear, and we are committed to addressing any legitimate copyright
          concerns quickly.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin: 25px 0 10px">
          How to Submit a Takedown Request
        </h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 15px">
          If you are a copyright owner, or authorized to act on behalf of a
          copyright owner, and you believe that content on OldSchoolGames.eu
          infringes your copyright, please send a written notice to:
        </p>
        <p style="
              margin-bottom: 20px;
              padding: 15px;
              background: rgba(var(--border-rgb), 0.2);
              border: 1px solid rgb(var(--border-rgb));
              border-radius: var(--border-radius);
            ">
          📧
          <a class="color-primary underline" href="mailto:contact@oldschoolgames.eu">contact@oldschoolgames.eu</a>
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin: 25px 0 10px">
          Your Notice Must Include
        </h2>
        <ol style="padding-left: 25px; line-height: 2.2; margin-bottom: 20px">
          <li>
            Your full legal name and contact information (email address)
          </li>
          <li>
            Identification of the copyrighted work you claim has been
            infringed
          </li>
          <li>
            The specific URL(s) on OldSchoolGames.eu where the allegedly
            infringing content is located
          </li>
          <li>
            A statement that you have a good-faith belief that the use of the
            material is not authorized by the copyright owner, its agent, or
            the law
          </li>
          <li>
            A statement that the information in your notice is accurate and,
            under penalty of perjury, that you are the copyright owner or
            authorized to act on the owner's behalf
          </li>
          <li>Your electronic or physical signature</li>
        </ol>

        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin: 25px 0 10px">Our Response</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 15px">
          Upon receipt of a valid takedown notice, we will:
        </p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 20px">
          <li>Review the notice within <strong>5 business days</strong></li>
          <li>
            Remove or disable access to the allegedly infringing content
            promptly if the claim is valid
          </li>
          <li>Notify you once the content has been removed</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 20px">
          <strong>Please note:</strong> Submitting a false or misleading DMCA
          notice may result in legal liability for damages, costs, and
          attorneys' fees.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin: 25px 0 10px">Counter-Notice</h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 15px">
          If you believe your content was removed in error, you may submit a
          counter-notice to the same email address with:
        </p>
        <ul style="padding-left: 20px; line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 20px">
          <li>Your contact information</li>
          <li>
            Identification of the removed content and its location before
            removal
          </li>
          <li>
            A statement under penalty of perjury that you have a good-faith
            belief the content was removed due to a mistake or
            misidentification
          </li>
          <li>Your signature</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-md" style="margin: 25px 0 10px">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          All copyright-related inquiries:
          <a class="color-primary underline" href="mailto:contact@oldschoolgames.eu">contact@oldschoolgames.eu</a>. For general information about the site, see our
          <a class="color-primary underline" href="/about">About page</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
  <%- include('right-sidebar') %> <%- include('footer') %>
</body>

</html>
